<H3> Concurrency Analysis </H3>
<UL>

<P><LI>
<A HREF="http://portal.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=225028&coll=portal&dl=ACM&CFID=12169447&CFTOKEN=41015364">
A Compact Petri Net Representation for Concurrent Programs</A>,
by Matthew B. Dwyer, Lori A. Clarke and Kari A. Nies in <i>Proceedings of the Seventeenth International 
Conference on Software Engineering</i>, pages 147-157, April 24-28, 1995, Seattle, WA.

<A HREF="http://www.ics.uci.edu/Arcadia/arcadia_papers/analysis/tbpns_abstract.html"> Abstract </A>
<P>
<LI> <A HREF="http://laser.cs.umass.edu/techreports/94-16.pdf"> A Compact Petri Net Representation for Ada Tasking Programs</A>,
  by Matthew B. Dwyer, Lori A. Clarke and Kari A. Nies in <i>University of Massachusetts COINS Technical Report 94-16, September 1994.</i>
  
  
  <P>
<LI>
<b>TIG-based Petri Nets for Modeling Ada Tasking</b>,
by Kari Forester, Lori Clarke, and Matthew Dwyer in
<i>University of Massachusetts COINS Technical Report 91-69, June 1991 (Masters Thesis).</i>
<A HREF="papers/tbpn_masters.html"> Abstract </A>

<P><LI>
<A HREF="http://portal.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=201080&coll=portal&dl=ACM&CFID=12169447&CFTOKEN=41015364">
A Concurrency Analysis Tool Suite for Ada Programs: Design, Rationale,
and Preliminary Experience</A>,
by Michal Young, Richard N. Taylor, David L. Levine, Kari A. Nies,
and Debra Brodbeck in
<i>ACM Transactions on Software Engineering and Methodology</i>, 4(1):65-106, January 1995.  
<A HREF="http://www.ics.uci.edu/Arcadia/arcadia_papers/analysis/cats_tosem_abstract.html"> Abstract </A>

<P><LI>
Young, M., R. Taylor, K. Forester, D. Brodbeck. 
<A HREF="http://portal.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=75331&coll=portal&dl=ACM&CFID=12169447&CFTOKEN=41015364">
Integrated concurrency analysis in a software development environment</A>. 
<em>Proceedings of the Third Symposium on Testing, Analysis, and 
Verification</em>, Key West, pp. 200ï¿½209 (December 1989).
</UL>
